    "text": "Your description reminds me of a <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Schmitt_trigger|Schmitt trigger> used in electronics. One can implement a Schmitt-trigger-like action in the digital domain with a state machine:\nS1: when a 0-&gt;1 event occurs, go to state S2.\nS2: when a 1-&gt;0 event occurs go back to state S1.\n(I think of the timer variant as a Schmitt trigger that deals with analog signals).",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "thread_ts": "1775134215.731019",
