    "ts": "1775135353.353819",
    "client_msg_id": "9c8ab54b-23ab-42b7-b004-ea968cef6e8d",
    "text": "Yes - it's exactly that! A throttle (or some variant of throttle - I'm also not familiar with precise terminology around those concepts). The thing is that this throttle can be used to prevent back-flow of information in reactive graphs. This allows reactive graphs with cycles &amp; multidirectional dataflow - which are otherwise finnicky and prone to oscillations to behave in a more robust fashion.",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "thread_ts": "1775053630.907069",
